  Diamond, Douglas W
Author-Name:  Verrecchia, Robert E
Title: 
 Disclosure, Liquidity, and the Cost of Capital.

Journal: Journal of Finance
Pages: 1325-59
Issue: 4
Volume: 46
Year: 1991
Month:  September 
Abstract:

 This paper shows that revealing public information to reduce information
 asymmetry can reduce a firm's cost of capital by attracting increased
 demand from large investors due to increased liquidity of its securities.
 Large firms will disclose more information since they benefit most.
 Disclosure also reduces the risk-bearing capacity available through market
 makers. If initial information asymmetry is large, reducing it will
 increase the current price of the security. However, the maximum current
 price occurs with some asymmetry of information: further reduction of
 information asymmetry accentuates the undesirable effects of exit from
 market making.


