Title: 
 The Valuation Effects of Private Placements of Convertible Debt.

Journal: Journal of Finance
Pages: 1925-32
Issue: 5
Volume: 46
Year: 1991
Month:  December 
Abstract:

 Share price reactions to announcements of sixty-one private placements of
 convertible debt securities are investigated and a significant positive
 average abnormal return of 1.80 percent is documented. This unique result
 contrasts with the negative average abnormal return associated with public
 sales of convertible debt securities. The positive effect on common
 shareholders' wealth appears to be related to the relative size of the
 private issue and unrelated to the degree to which the convertible bond is
 "out-of-the-money" at issuance.


