Abstract:

 Under corporate and personal taxation, the authors demonstrate that the
 relation between optimal debt level and business risk is roughly U-shaped.
 This result follows from the fact that the tax liability is an option
 portfolio that is long in the corporate tax option and short in the
 personal tax option. Therefore, the net effect of a change in business
 risk on the optimal debt level depends upon the relative magnitudes of the
 resultant marginal changes in the values of these two options. Results of
 empirical tests offer support for the predicted U-shaped relationship.


