  Maksimovic, Vojislav
Author-Name:  Zechner, Josef
Title: 
 Debt, Agency Costs, and Industry Equilibrium.

Journal: Journal of Finance
Pages: 1619-43
Issue: 5
Volume: 46
Year: 1991
Month:  December 
Abstract:

 The authors show that risk characteristics of projects' cash flows are
 endogenously determined by the investment decisions of all firms in an
 industry. As a result, in reasonable settings, financial structures which
 create incentives to expropriate debtholders by increasing risk are shown
 not to reduce value in an industry equilibrium. Without taxes, capital
 structure is irrelevant for individual firms despite its effect on the
 equityholders' incentives, but the maximum total amount of debt in the
 industry is determinate. Allowing for a corporate tax advantage of debt,
 capital structure becomes relevant but firms are indifferent between
 distinct alternative debt levels.


