  Longstaff, Francis A
Title: 
 Time Varying Term Premia and Traditional Hypotheses about the Term Structure.

Journal: Journal of Finance
Pages: 1307-14
Issue: 4
Volume: 45
Year: 1990
Month:  September 
Abstract:

 Empirical evidence of time varying term premia in bond returns is
 frequently interpreted as evidence against the expectations hypothesis.
 This paper shows that the expectations hypothesis can actually imply time
 varying term premia if the time frame for which the expectations
 hypothesis holds differs from the return measurement period. Furthermore,
 many of the properties of these term premia are consistent with those of
 observed term premia. These results are important because they imply that
 the case against the expectations hypothesis is weaker than claimed in the
 empirical literature.


