  Vijh, Anand M
Title: 
 Liquidity of the CBOE Equity Options.

Journal: Journal of Finance
Pages: 1157-79
Issue: 4
Volume: 45
Year: 1990
Month:  September 
Abstract:

 The author examines the CBOE option market depth and bid-ask spreads.
 Absence of price effects surrounding large option trades suggests
 excellent market depth. However, bid-ask spreads for the CBOE options and
 the NYSE stocks are nearly equal, even though an average option is
 equivalent to less than half a stock plus borrowing. The author explains
 this trade-off between market depth and bid-ask spreads on the CBOE and
 the NYSE by differences in market mechanisms. The author also shows that
 the adverse-selection component of the option spread, which measures the
 extent of information-related trading on the CBOE, is very small.


