Title: 
 Equity Issues and Stock Price Dynamics.

Journal: Journal of Finance
Pages: 1019-43
Issue: 4
Volume: 45
Year: 1990
Month:  September 
Abstract:

 This paper presents an information-theoretic, infinite-horizon model of
 the equity issue decision. The model predicts that equity issues on
 average are preceded by an abnormal positive return on the stock, although
 for some firms the issue is preceded by a loss; equity issues on average
 are preceded by an abnormal rise in the market; and the stock price drops
 at the announcement of an issue. The model provides a measure of the
 welfare cost of asymmetric information; the welfare loss may be small even
 if the price drop at issue announcement is large.


