Title: 
 Shareholder Preferences and Dividend Policy.

Journal: Journal of Finance
Pages: 993-1018
Issue: 4
Volume: 45
Year: 1990
Month:  September 
Abstract:

 This paper develops a theory of choice among alternative procedures for
 distributing cash from corporations to shareholders. Despite the
 preferential tax treatment of capital gains for individual investors, it
 is shown that a majority of a firm's shareholders may support a dividend
 payment for small distributions. For larger distributions, an open-market
 stock repurchase is likely to be preferred by a majority of shareholders
 and, for the largest distributions, tender offer repurchases dominate.


