Title: 
 The Quality Delivery Option in Treasury Bond Futures Contracts.

Journal: Journal of Finance
Pages: 1565-86
Issue: 5
Volume: 45
Year: 1990
Month:  December 
Abstract:

 This paper uses three methods to estimate quality option values for
 Chicago Board of Trade Treasury bond futures contracts. It presents
 evidence regarding payoffs from exercising this option at delivery,
 estimates from a T-bond futures pricing model that incorporates this
 option, and estimates obtained from an exchange option pricing formula.
 The results indicate that this option is worth considerably less than
 reported by A. Kane and A.  Marcus (1986). For example, payoffs obtained
 by switching from the bond cheapest to deliver three months prior to
 delivery to the one cheapest at time of delivery average less than 0.30
 percentage points of par.


