  MacKie-Mason, Jeffrey K
Title: 
 Do Taxes Affect Corporate Financing Decisions?

Journal: Journal of Finance
Pages: 1471-93
Issue: 5
Volume: 45
Year: 1990
Month:  December 
Abstract:

 This paper provides clear evidence of substantial tax effects on the
 choice between issuing debt or equity; most studies fail to find
 significant effects. The relationship between tax shields and debt policy
 is clarified. Other papers miss the fact that most tax shields have a
 negligible effect on the marginal tax rate for most firms. New predictions
 are strongly supported by an empirical analysis; the method is to study
 incremental financing decisions using discrete choice analysis. Previous
 researchers examined debt/equity ratios, but tests based on incremental
 decisions should have greater power.


