  Ikeda, Shinsuke
Title: 
 Arbitrage Asset Pricing under Exchange Risk.

Journal: Journal of Finance
Pages: 447-55
Issue: 1
Volume: 46
Year: 1991
Month:  March 
Abstract:

 This paper extends the arbitrage pricing theory to an international
 setting. Specifying a linear factor return-generating model in local
 currency terms, the author shows that the usual risk-diversification rule
 in the arbitrage pricing theory does not yield a riskless portfolio unless
 currency fluctuations obey the same factor model as asset returns. The
 author then considers an arbitrage portfolio whose exchange risk is hedged
 by foreign riskless bonds. Under the resulting no-arbitrage conditions,
 the expected returns are not on the same hyperplane, unlike the
 closed-economy arbitrage pricing theory, unless they are adjusted by the
 cost of exchange risk hedging.


