Title: 
 Production-Based Asset Pricing and the Link between Stock Returns and Economic Fluctuations.

Journal: Journal of Finance
Pages: 209-37
Issue: 1
Volume: 46
Year: 1991
Month:  March 
Abstract:

 This paper describes a production-based asset pricing model. It is
 analogous to the standard consumption-based model, but it uses producers
 and production functions in the place of consumers and utility functions.
 The model ties stock returns to investment returns (marginal rates of
 transformation), which are inferred from investment data via a production
 function. The production-based model is used to examine forecasts of stock
 returns by business-cycle related variables and the association of stock
 returns with subsequent economic activity.


