Title: 
 Intraday Price Change and Trading Volume Relations in the Stock and Stock Option Markets.

Journal: Journal of Finance
Pages: 191-220
Issue: 1
Volume: 45
Year: 1990
Month:  March 
Abstract:

 This study investigates intraday relations between price changes and
 trading volumes of options and stocks for a sample of firms whose options
 traded on the Chicago Board Options Exchange during the first quarter of
 1986. After purging the price change series of the effects of bid/ask
 spreads, multivariate time-series analysis is used to estimate the
 lead/lag relation between the price changes in the option and stock
 markets. The results indicate that price changes in the stock market lead
 the option market by as much as fifteen minutes. The analysis of trading
 volume indicates that the stock market lead may be even longer.


