Title: 
 On Viable Diffusion Price Processes of the Market Portfolio.

Journal: Journal of Finance
Pages: 673-89
Issue: 2
Volume: 45
Year: 1990
Month:  June 
Abstract:

 The assumption that the market portfolio follows a specified diffusion
 process implies, in a simple equilibrium framework, that the
 representative individual must have a certain utility function that is
 identified in the paper. Not every diffusion process is viable, i.e., can
 be "endogenized" to be the market portfolio's price process in such an
 equilibrium model. The paper provides necessary and sufficient conditions
 for viability that imply that viable diffusion processes constitute a
 rather restricted family.


