Title: 
 The Effect of Executive Stock Option Plans on Stockholders and Bondholders.

Journal: Journal of Finance
Pages: 617-27
Issue: 2
Volume: 45
Year: 1990
Month:  June 
Abstract:

 Executive stock option plans have asymmetric payoffs that could induce
 managers to take on more risk. Evidence from traded call options and stock
 return data supports this notion. Implicit share price variance, computed
 from the Black-Scholes options pricing model, and stock return variance
 increase after the approval of an executive stock option plan. The event
 is accompanied by a significant positive stock and a negative bond market
 reaction. This evidence is consistent with the notion that executive stock
 options may induce a wealth transfer from bondholders to stockholders.


