Abstract:

 In this paper, the authors investigate the effects of relative price
 variability on output and the stock market, and gauge the extent to which
 inflation proxies for relative price variability in stock-return-inflation
 regressions. The evidence shows that the negative stock-return-inflation
 relations proxy for the adverse effects of relative price variability on
 economic activity, particularly during the 1970s, when the United States
